      <h3>Step 1: Define Temperature Requirements</h3>

      <p>Identify what you'll transport:
      <br>• Frozen foods (-18°C to -25°C): Full refrigeration unit needed
      <br>• Chilled foods (+2°C to +8°C): Light refrigeration sufficient
      <br>• Mixed loads: Multi-temperature zone lorry required</p>

      <h3>Step 2: Calculate Revenue Potential</h3>

      <p>Research cold chain rates:
      <br>• Per km: RM2.50-RM4.00 (vs RM1.50-RM2.50 for standard cargo)
      <br>• Per trip: RM800-RM1,500 premium for temperature-controlled service
      <br>• Contract rates: Monthly retainer pricing common for dedicated cold chain</p>

      <h3>Step 3: Determine New vs Used</h3>

      <p>Consider:
      <br>• Budget constraints
      <br>• Warranty importance (new units have full warranty)
      <br>• Technology needs (newer units have advanced temperature control)
      <br>• Availability (used cold chain lorries scarce compared to standard)</p>

